sentences: Anthony Joseph Testa (born 31 March 1987) is an American choreographer, creative director, educator and dancer.
In 2002 Tony was picked by choreographer Brian Friedman to tour with Aaron Carter for his Jukebox tour.
Testa has choreographed for Britney Spears, and for Nickelodeon's Dance on Sunset (2008).
In 2010 he began choreographing for Kylie Minogue on her "All The Lovers", "Better Than Today" and "Get Outta My Way" music videos.
He was the Associate Director and choreographer for her Aphrodite: Les Folies Tour (2011).
In November 2011, Testa co-directed the opening of the American Music Awards with Wade Robson.

In 2012, Testa choreographed for the K-pop band Shinee in their music video "Sherlock (Clue + Note)", which earned the band  the award for Best Dance Performance Male Group at the 2012 Mnet Asian Music Awards.

Testa is a dance educator for both the New York City Dance Alliance and Monsters Of Hip Hop dance conventions, and a guest speaker at the TEDx conference in Los Angeles in June 2013.
